# proxymitm

A simple experimental MITM (Man-in-the-Middle) proxy implementation in Go. This is a toy project for learning and experimenting with HTTP/HTTPS interception.

## Features

- Basic HTTPS traffic interception
- Simple certificate handling
- Basic interceptors for:
  - Request/Response logging
  - Header/body modification
  - Simple filtering
  - Request tracking

## Note

This is an experimental project for learning purposes. It's not recommended for production use.

## Development

- Go 1.24 or later
- Uses GitHub Actions for CI/CD
- Includes comprehensive test coverage
- Follows Go best practices and coding standards
